	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_000850_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Copy of original historical 
<lb/><hi rend="underline">letter from <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> David Livingstone</persName></hi></p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p><space extent="4" unit="words"/><placeName>Cassange</placeName></p>
<lb/><p><space extent="4" unit="words"/>14<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi><choice><abbr>Feby</abbr><expan>February</expan></choice> 1855</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Gabriel</persName></p>
<lb/><p>Along with this I enclose the <bibl>map</bibl> 
<lb/>&amp; <bibl>letter</bibl> for <persName>Sir R. Murchison</persName><reg>.</reg>
<lb/>In opening it you will find it easy 
<lb/>if you will let it stand an hour or two 
<lb/>in a towel on which you sprinkled 
<lb/>some water previously.</p>
<lb/><p>The same process will enable you to 
<lb/>fold it again with facility</p>
<lb/><p>Please when you write to <persName>Lie<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">ut</hi></hi>
<lb/>Bedingfeld</persName> present my compliments 
<lb/>on his escape.</p>
<lb/><p>Fancy the <orgName>natives</orgName> in 1855 of the "new" 
<lb/>"earth", &amp; no more sea, digging up my 
<lb/>fossil manuscripts &amp; as much puzzled 
<lb/>to tell the situation of <placeName><country>Angola</country></placeName> as the 
<lb/><term type="occupation">Commentators</term> have been with the 
<lb/>whereabouts of the <placeName>Garden of Eden</placeName>. 
<lb/>As you are a <term type="occupation">lawyer</term> in embryo 
<lb/>(pardon) I suppose the decision that 
<lb/>a person born out of <placeName><country>England</country></placeName> is an 
<lb/>"alien"- will change your views a 
<lb/>little, I believe it was given in a 
<lb/>case of copyright.</p>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_000850_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/><fw type="pageno"><hi rend="underline">2.</hi><hi rend="underline">re <persName>Gabriel</persName></hi></fw>
<lb/><p><orgName><term type="nationality">English</term> parents</orgName> don't now produce 
<lb/><orgName><term type="nationality">English</term> children</orgName></p>
<lb/><p>Mine are therefore niggars - "<foreign xml:lang="und">moleques</foreign>"- 
<lb/>in fact for they were born in <placeName><bloc>Africa</bloc></placeName>
<lb/>Excuse the hotch potch note </p>
<lb/><p>Believe me ever most 
<lb/>affectionately yours </p>
<lb/><p>(sd.) <persName>David Livingstone </persName></p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Copied from original 
<lb/><persName>C. G. Reeve</persName></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><placeName><settlement type="city">London</settlement></placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><choice><abbr>Feby</abbr><expan>February</expan></choice> 1938 </p>
			
